    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-24T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-24T04:00:00-05:00" n="465"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1267a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Rangoon</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schnare</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-24T04:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 24, 1942—4 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. For Lt. Colonel St. John, <hi rend="smallcaps">Ammisca</hi> from Adams.<note
                        n="10" xml:id="d465fn10">Maj. Gen. Emory S. Adams, Adjutant General, U. S.
                        A.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Begin paraphrase. All lend-lease items of a critical nature at Rangoon should be
                    moved by you to the interior of China by every means available to you. The above
                    is a direction of the Secretary of War. To accomplish this lend-lease funds
                    necessary for wages, bonuses and transport may be obligated by you through Major
                    Haywood, such action on your part being authorized, as a military necessity. The
                    above is being communicated to Magruder. End paraphrase.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
